Inheritance => Reuse
eg.
Mobile ---> version
----> calling , msg
----> setalaram, light,camera

Keyword: extends
Single
class a
{
calling()
{
}
msg()
{
}
}
class b extends a
{
setalaram()
{
}
light()
{
}
camera()
{
}
}
class c extends b // Multilevel
{
}
class d extends c
{
}

Types
1. Single Inheritance => only one
2. Multilevel Inheritance => more than one level
3. Hierarchical=> one class => n no class
4. Hybrid
5. Multiple Inheritance(not supported in java) => Interface
Hierarchical
class a
{
}
class b extends a
{
}
class c extends a
{
}
Multiple
class a
{
}
class b
{
}
class c extends a,b // compile time error
{
}

Hierarchical
---> clg[name,code]
 ----> student[name,rollno,dept]
 ----> staff[name,staffid,dept]